    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Non-instructed Advocate - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_non-instructed_advocate">Non-Instructed Advocate</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_non-instructed_advocate">Non-Instructed Advocate</xref>
 assists 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 who are unable to communicate their views and wishes relating to the decision to be made.        </p>
    <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_non-instructed_advocate">Non-Instructed Advocate</xref>, see the Office of Public Guardian and 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 part of the 
              <xref href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/independent-mental-capacity-advocates" scope="external" format="html">gov.uk website.</xref>
    </p>
  </div>
